events.name: The Delta Riggs - Townsville - 28th July
events.description:
After their critically acclaimed fourth album ‘Modern Pressure’, which saw the band tour arena with Billy Idol and Sticky Fingers, The Delta Riggs are on the road once again, and the band's energy is the best it’s ever been.

The Melbourne rockers’ psychedelic, cosmic rock ‘n roll anthems transport listeners to far-off lands and portals through other dimensions, while front-man Elliott Hammond delivers his signature rich, raspy vocals that dip, howl, screech and wail, with unparalleled magnetism.

Renowned for pumping out high-energy jams, and ferocious, sweat-soaked live shows, this Rolling Stone Magazine's "Live Act Of The Year" alumni will land at Otherwise Bar brimming with their blend of cheeky swagger, psychedelic sounds, and unbridled energy.


Supported by: Good Grief

events.name: Tourist
events.description:
William Phillips, also known as Tourist, is a multi-talented musician and producer who has worked with some of the biggest names in the industry. He won a Grammy Award for Song of the Year in 2015 for his work on Sam Smith's "Stay With Me," and has since released three critically acclaimed albums and numerous EPs. 

Tourist's music is a kaleidoscopic fusion of dance and electronic genres, combining elements of garage, house, and techno, as well as pop and R&B influences. His upcoming album, "Inside Out," was born out of grief but exists as a testament to his ability to create tender and uplifting music in moments of darkness, with sparkling fragments of garage grooves and French filter house. 

His live show has captivated audiences at Coachella, Glastonbury and Village Underground, and now Tourist is set to take his performance to new heights with a show that promises to make his one wish come true: to feel everything, with everyone, through dance music.

This show is presented as part of Open Season - a curated program of music and art running across The Princess Theatre and The Tivoli during winter. Open Season is supported through Arts Queensland, the Live Music Australia Fund and the Restart Investment to Sustain and Expand (RISE) Fund – initiatives of the Australian Government.

events.name: Small Fry Rock feat. Katie Noonan & Darren Middleton
events.description:
Featuring Katie Noonan & Darren Middleton

ON SALE - 10AM FRIDAY 16 JUNE

Designed for music loving families who want to introduce their small fries to music they know and love. Family friendly and covid safe! 

Doors 11am. Music from 11:30am. Wrapped by 1pm. 

Over the past 20 years, five-time ARIA award-winning artist Katie Noonan has proven herself one of Australia’s most hardworking, versatile and prolific artists. Named one of the greatest Australian singers of all time by the Herald Sun, Katie has produced 24 studio albums over her career with seven x platinum record sales under her belt and 27 ARIA award nominations that span diverse genres. Katie has performed for royalty, national and international leaders, and blazed a trail for young women artists. Music, for Katie, is a lifelong lesson, a generous act of giving, and a means to change the world.

Darren Middleton is best known from his previous life as guitarist and songwriter for Australian band, Powderfinger. After the band's split in 2010, Middleton set up shop in Melbourne's creative hub as a producer. This production work would sow the seeds of his solo artist career, opening endless doors and connections that would lead him to create debut album 'Translations'. Darren's album 'HOME' marks his latest full-length project, showcasing his best, most authentic material to date.

See you on the dance floor!
********
General Questions & Information
- Pram parking available in the foyer of the venue.
- Packed food and snacks are allowed into the venue. Bistro also available on the day offering a children's menu.
- Colouring stations set up throughout the beer garden.
- Quiet zone available (upstairs).
- Volume is set at a safe level for children and carefully monitored throughout the event. Recommended use of hearing protection/baby ear muffs if you have any concerns.
- Content warning. Although we ask our Artists to keep it PG, we can't always ensure it will stay that way once the event has begun. 
- Parents remain responsible for their children at all times.

venues.name: The Princess Theatre

boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Please note venue collection is only available from The Princess Theatre box office once doors have opened on the night of the performance.

venues.parkingDetail: There is no on-site parking at The Princess, and street parking is very limited. There is a paid, undercover car parking at Princess Parking (not affiliated with The Princess Theatre). The venue recommends catching public transport or getting dropped off.

generalInfo.childRule: The Princess Theatre presents both Over 18 Only and All Ages events. Patrons are advised to check the event pages for age information specific to each event. Please note age restrictions are strictly enforced.
